cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a novel technique for satisfiability checking of formulae written in Linear Temporal Logic with Both future and past operators and atomic formulae belonging to constraint system D (CLTLB(D) for short). 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses an encoding of CLTLB(D) formulae into QF-EUD, which is a theory of quantifier-free equality and uninterpreted functions combined with D. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper mentions the use of bounded model-checking and SAT-solvers as an alternative to automata-theoretic approaches to model-checking, which are commonly used in machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possibility as the paper discusses a technique for solving the satisfiability problem for CLTLB(D) formulae through SMT-solving techniques, which are commonly used in AI. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possibility as the paper mentions the implementation of the technique in the Zot formal verification tool, which is a software engineering tool.
